.TH "wget" "1" "" "seed 0.1.0"
.SH NAME
wget \- retrieve files over HTTP and HTTPS
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B wget [OPTIONS] URL...
.SH DESCRIPTION
wget fetches each URL and writes the response body to standard output or a file.
.PP
POST requests can be sent with inline data via \-\-post\-data or by reading the request body from a file with \-\-post\-file.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-q
Suppress normal output.
.TP
.B \-O FILE
Write the response body to FILE instead of a derived filename.
.TP
.B \-P DIR
Write output files below DIR.
.TP
.B \-k, \-\-no\-check\-certificate
Disable TLS certificate verification.
.TP
.B \-\-ca\-certificate FILE
Load trusted root certificates from FILE.
.TP
.B \-\-header 'Name: Value'
Add an HTTP request header. May be repeated.
.TP
.B \-\-post\-data DATA
Send DATA as the POST request body.
.TP
.B \-\-post\-file FILE
Read the POST request body from FILE.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Show a short usage summary.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B wget \-q \-O\- https://example.com/
Write the response body to standard output.
.TP
.B wget \-\-post\-file payload.json \-\-header 'Content\-Type: application/json' https://example.com/api
Send a JSON request body loaded from payload.json.
.SH SEE ALSO
man(1)
